    <title>Frequently Asked Questions - Ai Fitness Plan Generator</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Get answers to frequently asked questions about Ai Fitness Plan Generator. Learn about pricing, features, compatibility, and more.">
    
    <!-- JSON-LD Schema for FAQPage -->
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q1: Is AI Fitness Plan Generator free to use?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, AI Fitness Plan Generator is completely free to use. You can generate up to 3 workout plans per day without creating an account. For unlimited generations and the ability to save/export plans, you can create a free account. There are no hidden fees or premium features locked behind a paywall. - Free tier: 3 generations/day, no account needed - Registered users: Unlimited generations, save/export features - Pricing: $0 forever (ad-supported), optional $4.99/month ad-free upgrade ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q2: How accurate are the generated fitness plans?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The generated plans are based on exercise science principles and trained on 5,000+ professionally designed workout programs. While the AI provides a solid foundation, you should consult a certified trainer for form checks. The plans achieve ~85% accuracy for general fitness goals and ~70% for specialized goals like powerlifting or bodybuilding. - Training data: 5,000+ professional workout programs, ACSM guidelines - Accuracy: 85% for general fitness, 70% for specialized training - Validation: Each plan is reviewed by certified trainers before being added to the training set ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q3: Can I customize the generated workout plan?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, after the AI generates your initial plan, you can customize it. You can swap exercises, adjust set/rep ranges, change rest periods, and modify the weekly schedule. The AI will then re-optimize the plan based on your changes. You can also specify equipment limitations before generation. - Customization options: Exercise swap, set/rep adjustment, rest periods, schedule changes - Equipment settings: None, dumbbells only, full gym, bodyweight, resistance bands - Re-optimization: AI adjusts the plan in real-time as you make changes ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q4: How long does it take to generate a fitness plan?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The AI generates a complete fitness plan in under 30 seconds. This includes a 4-12 week workout schedule, exercise descriptions, sets and reps, and rest recommendations. You can start your first workout immediately after generation. No waiting, no complex setup process. - Generation time: 10-30 seconds average - Output: 4-12 week plan, 3-6 workouts per week, exercise descriptions - Immediate start: Download PDF or view in browser and begin working out ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q5: Can I generate plans for specific fitness goals?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, the AI supports 12 specific fitness goals: muscle gain, fat loss, strength, endurance, powerlifting, bodybuilding, functional fitness, weight loss maintenance, post-pregnancy fitness, senior fitness, athletic performance, and general health. Each goal uses different algorithms optimized for that specific outcome. - Supported goals: 12 goal types with specialized algorithms - Customization: Set primary and secondary goals - Adaptation: Plan adjusts if you change goals mid-program ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q6: Does the generator create nutrition plans too?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, you can optionally include a nutrition plan with your workout plan. The AI generates a meal plan based on your calorie target, macronutrient preferences, and dietary restrictions. The nutrition plan includes a 7-day meal schedule, recipes, and a grocery list. This feature is available for registered users. - Nutrition features: Meal plan, recipes, grocery list, macro tracking - Dietary options: Keto, vegan, vegetarian, paleo, Mediterranean, etc. - Availability: Registered users (free account required) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q7: Can I export the generated plan to PDF or print it?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, you can export your generated plan as a PDF, print it, or send it to your email. Registered users can also sync plans to Google Sheets or export to fitness apps like MyFitnessPal and Strong. The PDF includes exercise descriptions, illustrations, and a workout log template. - Export formats: PDF, Print, Email, Google Sheets, CSV - App integration: MyFitnessPal, Strong, Fitbod, Apple Health - PDF contents: Exercise list, descriptions, illustrations, workout log ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q8: Is AI Fitness Plan Generator suitable for women?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Absolutely. The AI creates plans that are equally effective for women and men. You can specify your gender during setup, and the AI will adjust recommendations based on typical physiological differences (e.g., different recovery rates, hormonal considerations). The plans are designed by certified female trainers to ensure they're appropriate and effective. - Gender-specific adjustments: Recovery time, exercise selection, nutrition targets - Trainer input: Plans reviewed by certified female trainers - Goals: Supports women-specific goals like post-pregnancy fitness, menopause fitness ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q9: What if I don't know my fitness level?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The generator includes a fitness level assessment quiz that takes 2 minutes. It asks about your exercise history, current activity level, and strength benchmarks (e.g., \"How many push-ups can you do?\"). Based on your answers, the AI determines whether you're a beginner, intermediate, or advanced athlete. - Assessment: 10-question quiz, 2 minutes - Benchmarks: Push-ups, squat depth, plank hold time, mile run time - Output: Beginner, intermediate, or advanced classification ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q10: How often should I regenerate my fitness plan?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most users should regenerate their plan every 8-12 weeks to prevent plateaus and maintain progress. The AI automatically suggests a plan update when it detects your progress has stalled. You can also manually regenerate at any time. The system saves your previous plans so you can return to them later. - Recommended frequency: Every 8-12 weeks - Plateau detection: AI monitors your progress and suggests updates - Plan history: All previous plans saved in your account ---"
      }
    }
  ]
}
